{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went off the line-- out of 1,000 infantry man we went on the line with, we went off with 120 or 130 who were still walking when we left.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's in two weeks of fighting.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we did front-line-- every doctor's called a surgeon in the Army.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It doesn't mean you're a specialist or anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were front line.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We would get the wounded, sometimes run out and get them ourselves, or go with the aid men, get them in some-- and get-- our job was to set up an aid station as close to the line as we could.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It came as a real shock in the Medical Field Service School in 1942 when they said, gentleman-- we all thought it would be in a hospital or something-- gentlemen, be sure to get the wounded in defilade.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we said, what's defilade?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said, that's out of the line of direct fire from machine guns.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we said, oh, yeah?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So you get them in shelter, like a cellar.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In Europe, we'd find these ruined buildings, cellars, holes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There's always something to crawl into, cover it over, get a little stove going for heat for the wounded.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the aid men would bring them in on the half-tracks and litter Jeeps.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We'd stop bleeding, splint bones, sometimes amputate limbs, and give blood plasma.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They couldn't give blood that far forward in those days, but they had plasma, which was made up in a powdered bottle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it-- you diluted it with a vacuum bottle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then you could stick a soldier rifle on the ground by the bayonet, hang the plasma, and run it in by vein.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We could do things like that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And very front line, very rough, immediate lifesaving intervention is what we did.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
